9687  EmitBranchOffset(instr.optional.depth);
9688  } else {
9689  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BranchOnNullWithParams);
9690  ValueType value_type = RefPop(); // pop condition
9691  EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
9692  // Remove nullability.
9693  if (value_type.kind() == kRefNull) {
9694  value_type = ValueType::Ref(value_type.heap_type());
9695  }
9696  RefPush(value_type); // re-push condition value
9697 
9698  // Emit code offset to branch to if the condition is not true.
9699  const uint32_t if_false_code_offset = CurrentCodePos();
9700  Emit(&if_false_code_offset, sizeof(if_false_code_offset));
9701 
9702  uint32_t stack_top = stack_.back();
9703  RefPop(false); // Drop the null reference.
9704 
9705  StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(target_branch_index, kExprBrIf);
9706 
9707  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Branch);
9708  EmitBranchOffset(instr.optional.depth);
9709 
9710  stack_.push_back(stack_top); // re-push non-null ref on top of stack
9711 
9712  // Patch the 'if-false' offset with the correct jump offset.
9713  int32_t delta = CurrentCodePos() - if_false_code_offset;
9714  base::WriteUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(
9715  reinterpret_cast<Address>(code_.data() + if_false_code_offset),
9716  delta);
9717  }
9718  break;
9719  }
9720  case kExprBrOnNonNull: {
9721  DCHECK_EQ(mode, kS2S);
9722  int32_t target_branch_index = GetTargetBranch(instr.optional.depth);
9723  const WasmBytecodeGenerator::BlockData& target_block_data =
9724  blocks_[target_branch_index];
9725  if (HasVoidSignature(target_block_data)) {
9726  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BranchOnNonNull);
9727  ValueType value_type = RefPop(); // pop condition
9728  EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
9729  RefPush(value_type); // re-push condition value
9730  // Emit code offset to branch to if the condition is true.
9731  EmitBranchOffset(instr.optional.depth);
9732 
9733  RefPop(false); // Drop the null reference.
9734  } else {
9735  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BranchOnNonNullWithParams);
9736  ValueType value_type = RefPop(); // pop condition
9737  EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
9738  RefPush(value_type); // re-push condition value
9739 
9740  // Emit code offset to branch to if the condition is not true.
9741  const uint32_t if_false_code_offset = CurrentCodePos();
9742  Emit(&if_false_code_offset, sizeof(if_false_code_offset));
9743 
9744  StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(target_branch_index, kExprBrIf);
9745 
9746  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Branch);
9747  EmitBranchOffset(instr.optional.depth);
9748 
9749  // Patch the 'if-false' offset with the correct jump offset.
9750  int32_t delta = CurrentCodePos() - if_false_code_offset;
9751  base::WriteUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(
9752  reinterpret_cast<Address>(code_.data() + if_false_code_offset),
9753  delta);
9754 
9755  RefPop(false); // Drop the null reference.
9756  }
9757  break;
9758  }
9759  case kExprBrOnCast: {
9760  const BranchOnCastData& br_on_cast_data = instr.optional.br_on_cast_data;
9761  const int32_t target_branch_index =
9762  GetTargetBranch(br_on_cast_data.label_depth);
9763  bool null_succeeds = br_on_cast_data.res_is_null;
9764  const ValueType target_type = ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
9765  HeapType::FromBits(br_on_cast_data.target_type_bit_fields),
9766  null_succeeds ? kNullable : kNonNullable);
9767 
9768  const ValueType obj_type = slots_[stack_.back()].value_type;
9769  DCHECK(obj_type.is_object_reference());
9770 
9771  // This logic ensures that code generation can assume that functions can
9772  // only be cast to function types, and data objects to data types.
9773  if (V8_UNLIKELY(
9774  TypeCheckAlwaysSucceeds(obj_type, target_type.heap_type()))) {
9775  StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(target_branch_index, kExprBrOnCast);
9776  // The branch will still not be taken on null if not {null_succeeds}.
9777  if (obj_type.is_nullable() && !null_succeeds) {
9778  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BranchOnNull);
9779  RefPop(); // pop condition
9780  EmitRefValueType(obj_type.raw_bit_field());
9781  RefPush(target_type); // re-push condition value with a new HeapType.
9782  EmitBranchOffset(br_on_cast_data.label_depth);
9783  } else {
9784  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Branch);
9785  EmitBranchOffset(br_on_cast_data.label_depth);
9786  }
9787  } else if (V8_LIKELY(!TypeCheckAlwaysFails(
9788  obj_type, target_type.heap_type(), null_succeeds))) {
9789  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BranchOnCast);
9790  EmitI32Const(null_succeeds);
9791  HeapType br_on_cast_data_target_type(
9792  HeapType::FromBits(br_on_cast_data.target_type_bit_fields));
9793  EmitI32Const(br_on_cast_data_target_type.is_index()
9794  ? br_on_cast_data_target_type.raw_bit_field()
9795  : target_type.heap_type().raw_bit_field());
9796  ValueType value_type = RefPop();
9797  EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
9798  RefPush(value_type);
9799  // Emit code offset to branch to if the condition is not true.
9800  const uint32_t no_branch_code_offset = CurrentCodePos();
9801  Emit(&no_branch_code_offset, sizeof(no_branch_code_offset));
9802  StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(target_branch_index, kExprBrOnCast);
9803  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Branch);
9804  EmitBranchOffset(br_on_cast_data.label_depth);
9805  // Patch the 'if-false' offset with the correct jump offset.
9806  int32_t delta = CurrentCodePos() - no_branch_code_offset;
9807  base::WriteUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(
9808  reinterpret_cast<Address>(code_.data() + no_branch_code_offset),
9809  delta);
9810  }
9811  break;
9812  }
9813  case kExprBrOnCastFail: {
9814  const BranchOnCastData& br_on_cast_data = instr.optional.br_on_cast_data;
9815  int32_t target_branch_index =
9816  GetTargetBranch(br_on_cast_data.label_depth);
9817  bool null_succeeds = br_on_cast_data.res_is_null;
9818  HeapType br_on_cast_data_target_type =
9819  HeapType::FromBits(br_on_cast_data.target_type_bit_fields);
9820  const ValueType target_type =
9821  ValueType::RefMaybeNull(br_on_cast_data_target_type,
9822  null_succeeds ? kNullable : kNonNullable);
9823 
9824  const ValueType obj_type = slots_[stack_.back()].value_type;
9825  DCHECK(obj_type.is_object_reference());
9826 
9827  // This logic ensures that code generation can assume that functions can
9828  // only be cast to function types, and data objects to data types.
9829  if (V8_UNLIKELY(TypeCheckAlwaysFails(obj_type, target_type.heap_type(),
9830  null_succeeds))) {
9831  StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(target_branch_index, kExprBrOnCast);
9832  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Branch);
9833  EmitBranchOffset(br_on_cast_data.label_depth);
9834  } else if (V8_UNLIKELY(TypeCheckAlwaysSucceeds(
9835  obj_type, target_type.heap_type()))) {
9836  // The branch can still be taken on null.
9837  if (obj_type.is_nullable() && !null_succeeds) {
9838  StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(target_branch_index,
9839  kExprBrOnCast);
9840  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BranchOnNull);
9841  RefPop(); // pop condition
9842  EmitRefValueType(obj_type.raw_bit_field());
9843  RefPush(target_type); // re-push condition value with a new HeapType.
9844  EmitBranchOffset(br_on_cast_data.label_depth);
9845  } else {
9846  // Fallthrough.
9847  }
9848  } else {
9849  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BranchOnCastFail);
9850  EmitI32Const(null_succeeds);
9851  EmitI32Const(br_on_cast_data_target_type.is_index()
9852  ? br_on_cast_data_target_type.raw_bit_field()
9853  : target_type.heap_type().raw_bit_field());
9854  ValueType value_type = RefPop();
9855  EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
9856  RefPush(value_type);
9857  // Emit code offset to branch to if the condition is not true.
9858  const uint32_t no_branch_code_offset = CurrentCodePos();
9859  Emit(&no_branch_code_offset, sizeof(no_branch_code_offset));
9860  StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(target_branch_index, kExprBrOnCast);
9861  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Branch);
9862  EmitBranchOffset(br_on_cast_data.label_depth);
9863  // Patch the 'if-false' offset with the correct jump offset.
9864  int32_t delta = CurrentCodePos() - no_branch_code_offset;
9865  base::WriteUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(
9866  reinterpret_cast<Address>(code_.data() + no_branch_code_offset),
9867  delta);
9868  }
9869  break;
9870  }
9871  case kExprBrTable: {
9872  if (mode == kR2S) {
9873  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_BrTable);
9874  } else {
9875  DCHECK_EQ(mode, kS2S);
9876  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BrTable);
9877  I32Pop(); // branch label
9878  }
9879 
9880  // We emit the following bytecode for a br_table instruction:
9881  // s2s_BrTable handler id
9882  // (uint32) labels_count
9883  // (uint32) offset branch 0
9884  // (uint32) offset branch 1
9885  // ...
9886  // (uint32) offset branch labels_count - 1
9887  // (uint32) offset branch labels_count (default branch)
9888  // { Branch 0 slots }
9889  // { Branch 1 slots }
9890  // ...
9891  // { Branch labels_count slots }
9892  //
9893  // Where each {Branch i slots} contains the slots to execute a Branch
9894  // instruction:
9895  // { CopySlots for branch results, if present }
9896  // s2s_Branch handler id
9897  // (uint32) branch_offset (to be patched later)
9898  //
9899  const uint32_t labels_count = instr.optional.br_table.table_count;
9900  EmitI32Const(labels_count);
9901  uint32_t labels_offset_start = CurrentCodePos();
9902  for (uint32_t i = 0; i <= labels_count; i++) {
9903  // Here we don't know what will be the offset of this branch yet, so we
9904  // pass the current bytecode position as offset. This value will be
9905  // overwritten in the next loop.
9906  const uint32_t label_offset = CurrentCodePos();
9907  Emit(&label_offset, sizeof(label_offset));
9908  }
9909  for (uint32_t i = 0; i <= labels_count; i++) {
9910  uint32_t label =
9911  br_table_labels_[instr.optional.br_table.labels_index + i];
9912  int32_t target_branch_index = GetTargetBranch(label);
9913  uint32_t branch_code_start = CurrentCodePos();
9914  StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(target_branch_index, kExprBrTable);
9915 
9916  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Branch);
9917  EmitBranchTableOffset(label, CurrentCodePos());
9918 
9919  // Patch the branch offset with the correct jump offset.
9920  uint32_t label_offset = labels_offset_start + i * sizeof(uint32_t);
9921  int32_t delta = branch_code_start - label_offset;
9922  base::WriteUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(
9923  reinterpret_cast<Address>(code_.data() + label_offset), delta);
9924  }
9925  SetUnreachableMode();
9926  break;
9927  }
9928  case kExprReturn: {
9929  Return();
9930  SetUnreachableMode();
9931  break;
9932  }
9933  case kExprCallFunction:
9934  case kExprReturnCall: {
9935  uint32_t function_index = instr.optional.index;
9936  const FunctionSig* sig = GetFunctionSignature(function_index);
9937 
9938  // Layout of a frame:
9939  // ------------------
9940  // stack slot #N-1 ‾\
9941  // ... |
9942  // stack slot #0 _/
9943  // local #L-1 ‾\
9944  // ... |
9945  // local #0 _/
9946  // const #C-1 ‾\
9947  // ... |
9948  // const #0 _/
9949  // param #P-1 ‾\
9950  // ... |
9951  // param #0 _/
9952  // return #R-1 ‾\
9953  // ... |
9954  // return #0 _/
9955  // ------------------
9956 
9957  const bool is_imported = (module_->functions[function_index].imported);
9958  const bool is_tail_call = (instr.opcode == kExprReturnCall);
9959  uint32_t slot_offset = GetStackFrameSize() * kSlotSize;
9960  uint32_t ref_stack_fp_offset = ref_slots_count_;
9961 
9962  std::vector<uint32_t> rets_slots;
9963  rets_slots.resize(sig->return_count());
9964  for (size_t index = 0; index < sig->return_count(); index++) {
9965  rets_slots[index] = is_tail_call ? static_cast<uint32_t>(index)
9966  : CreateSlot(sig->GetReturn(index));
9967  }
9968 
9969  InitSlotsForFunctionArgs(sig, false);
9970 
9971  if (is_imported) {
9972  if (is_tail_call) {
9973  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_ReturnCallImportedFunction, instr.pc);
9974  EmitSlotOffset(WasmBytecode::RetsSizeInSlots(sig) * kSlotSize);
9975  EmitSlotOffset(WasmBytecode::ArgsSizeInSlots(sig) * kSlotSize);
9976  EmitI32Const(WasmBytecode::RefRetsCount(sig));
9977  EmitI32Const(WasmBytecode::RefArgsCount(sig));
9978  } else {
9979  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_CallImportedFunction, instr.pc);
9980  }
9981  } else {
9982  if (is_tail_call) {
9983  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_ReturnCall, instr.pc);
9984  EmitSlotOffset(WasmBytecode::RetsSizeInSlots(sig) * kSlotSize);
9985  EmitSlotOffset(WasmBytecode::ArgsSizeInSlots(sig) * kSlotSize);
9986  EmitI32Const(WasmBytecode::RefRetsCount(sig));
9987  EmitI32Const(WasmBytecode::RefArgsCount(sig));
9988  } else {
9989  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_CallFunction, instr.pc);
9990  }
9991  }
9992  EmitI32Const(function_index);
9993  EmitStackIndex(static_cast<uint32_t>(stack_.size()));
9994  EmitSlotOffset(slot_offset);
9995  EmitRefStackIndex(ref_stack_fp_offset);
9996 
9997  // Function arguments are popped from the stack.
9998  for (size_t index = sig->parameter_count(); index > 0; index--) {
9999  Pop(sig->GetParam(index - 1).kind(), false);
10000  }
10001 
10002 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
10003  if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
10004  EmitSlotOffset(rets_slots.empty()
10005  ? 0
10006  : slots_[rets_slots[0]].slot_offset * kSlotSize);
10007  }
10008 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
10009 
10010  if (!is_tail_call) {
10011  eh_data_.RecordPotentialExceptionThrowingInstruction(instr.opcode,
10012  CurrentCodePos());
10013  }
10014 
10015  // Function results are pushed to the stack.
10016  for (size_t index = 0; index < sig->return_count(); index++) {
10017  const ValueType value_type = sig->GetReturn(index);
10018  const ValueKind kind = value_type.kind();
10019  switch (kind) {
10020  case kI32:
10021  case kI64:
10022  case kF32:
10023  case kF64:
10024  case kS128:
10025  case kRef:
10026  case kRefNull:
10027  PushSlot(rets_slots[index]);
10028  SetSlotType(stack_top_index(), value_type);
10029  break;
10030  default:
10031  UNREACHABLE();
10032  }
10033  }
10034 
10035  // If this is a tail call, the following instructions in this block are
10036  // unreachable.
10037  if (is_tail_call) {
10038  SetUnreachableMode();
10039  }
10040 
10041  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10042  }
10043  case kExprCallIndirect:
10044  case kExprReturnCallIndirect: {
10045  const FunctionSig* sig = module_->signature(
10046  ModuleTypeIndex({instr.optional.indirect_call.sig_index}));
10047 
10048  const bool is_tail_call = (instr.opcode == kExprReturnCallIndirect);
10049  uint32_t slot_offset = GetStackFrameSize() * kSlotSize;
10050  uint32_t ref_stack_fp_offset = ref_slots_count_;
10051 
10052  // Reserve space for return values.
10053  std::vector<uint32_t> rets_slots;
10054  rets_slots.resize(sig->return_count());
10055  for (size_t index = 0; index < sig->return_count(); index++) {
10056  rets_slots[index] = is_tail_call ? static_cast<uint32_t>(index)
10057  : CreateSlot(sig->GetReturn(index));
10058  }
10059 
10060  InitSlotsForFunctionArgs(sig, true);
10061 
10062  bool is_table64 =
10063  module_->tables[instr.optional.indirect_call.table_index]
10064  .is_table64();
10065 
10066  if (is_tail_call) {
10067  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_ReturnCallIndirect,
10068  s2s_ReturnCallIndirect64, is_table64,
10069  instr.pc);
10070  EmitSlotOffset(WasmBytecode::RetsSizeInSlots(sig) * kSlotSize);
10071  EmitSlotOffset(WasmBytecode::ArgsSizeInSlots(sig) * kSlotSize);
10072  EmitI32Const(WasmBytecode::RefRetsCount(sig));
10073  EmitI32Const(WasmBytecode::RefArgsCount(sig));
10074  } else {
10075  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_CallIndirect, s2s_CallIndirect64,
10076  is_table64, instr.pc);
10077  }
10078 
10079  // Pops the index of the function to call.
10080  is_table64 ? I64Pop() : I32Pop();
10081 
10082  EmitI32Const(instr.optional.indirect_call.table_index);
10083  EmitI32Const(instr.optional.indirect_call.sig_index);
10084 
10085  EmitStackIndex(stack_size());
10086  EmitSlotOffset(slot_offset);
10087  EmitRefStackIndex(ref_stack_fp_offset);
10088 
10089  // Function arguments are popped from the stack.
10090  for (size_t index = sig->parameter_count(); index > 0; index--) {
10091  Pop(sig->GetParam(index - 1).kind(), false);
10092  }
10093 
10094 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
10095  if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
10096  EmitSlotOffset(rets_slots.empty()
10097  ? 0
10098  : slots_[rets_slots[0]].slot_offset * kSlotSize);
10099  }
10100 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
10101 
10102  if (!is_tail_call) {
10103  eh_data_.RecordPotentialExceptionThrowingInstruction(instr.opcode,
10104  CurrentCodePos());
10105  }
10106 
10107  // Function result is pushed to the stack.
10108  for (size_t index = 0; index < sig->return_count(); index++) {
10109  ValueType value_type = sig->GetReturn(index);
10110  switch (value_type.kind()) {
10111  case kI32:
10112  case kI64:
10113  case kF32:
10114  case kF64:
10115  case kS128:
10116  case kRef:
10117  case kRefNull:
10118  PushSlot(rets_slots[index]);
10119  SetSlotType(stack_top_index(), value_type);
10120  break;
10121  default:
10122  UNREACHABLE();
10123  }
10124  }
10125 
10126  // If this is a tail call, the following instructions in this block are
10127  // unreachable.
10128  if (is_tail_call) {
10129  SetUnreachableMode();
10130  }
10131 
10132  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10133  }
10134 
10135  case kExprCallRef:
10136  case kExprReturnCallRef: {
10137  const FunctionSig* sig =
10138  module_->signature(ModuleTypeIndex({instr.optional.index}));
10139  const bool is_tail_call = (instr.opcode == kExprReturnCallRef);
10140  uint32_t slot_offset = GetStackFrameSize() * kSlotSize;
10141  uint32_t ref_stack_fp_offset = ref_slots_count_;
10142 
10143  // Reserve space for return values.
10144  std::vector<uint32_t> rets_slots;
10145  rets_slots.resize(sig->return_count());
10146  for (size_t index = 0; index < sig->return_count(); index++) {
10147  rets_slots[index] = is_tail_call ? static_cast<uint32_t>(index)
10148  : CreateSlot(sig->GetReturn(index));
10149  }
10150 
10151  InitSlotsForFunctionArgs(sig, true);
10152 
10153  if (is_tail_call) {
10154  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_ReturnCallRef, instr.pc);
10155  EmitSlotOffset(WasmBytecode::RetsSizeInSlots(sig) * kSlotSize);
10156  EmitSlotOffset(WasmBytecode::ArgsSizeInSlots(sig) * kSlotSize);
10157  EmitI32Const(WasmBytecode::RefRetsCount(sig));
10158  EmitI32Const(WasmBytecode::RefArgsCount(sig));
10159  } else {
10160  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_CallRef, instr.pc);
10161  }
10162 
10163  // Pops the function to call.
10164  RefPop();
10165 
10166  EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index); // Signature index.
10167  EmitStackIndex(stack_size());
10168  EmitSlotOffset(slot_offset);
10169  EmitRefStackIndex(ref_stack_fp_offset);
10170 
10171  // Function arguments are popped from the stack.
10172  for (size_t index = sig->parameter_count(); index > 0; index--) {
10173  Pop(sig->GetParam(index - 1).kind(), false);
10174  }
10175 
10176 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
10177  if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
10178  EmitSlotOffset(rets_slots.empty()
10179  ? 0
10180  : slots_[rets_slots[0]].slot_offset * kSlotSize);
10181  }
10182 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
10183 
10184  if (!is_tail_call) {
10185  eh_data_.RecordPotentialExceptionThrowingInstruction(instr.opcode,
10186  CurrentCodePos());
10187  }
10188 
10189  // Function result is pushed to the stack.
10190  for (size_t index = 0; index < sig->return_count(); index++) {
10191  const ValueType value_type = sig->GetReturn(index);
10192  const ValueKind kind = value_type.kind();
10193  switch (kind) {
10194  case kI32:
10195  case kI64:
10196  case kF32:
10197  case kF64:
10198  case kS128:
10199  case kRef:
10200  case kRefNull:
10201  PushSlot(rets_slots[index]);
10202  SetSlotType(stack_top_index(), value_type);
10203  break;
10204  default:
10205  UNREACHABLE();
10206  }
10207  }
10208 
10209  // If this is a tail call, the following instructions in this block are
10210  // unreachable.
10211  if (is_tail_call) {
10212  SetUnreachableMode();
10213  }
10214 
10215  return RegMode::kNoReg;
10216  }
10217 
10218  case kExprDrop: {
10219  switch (top_stack_slot_type) {
10220  case kI32:
10221  switch (mode) {
10222  case kR2R:
10223  case kS2R:
10224  UNREACHABLE();
10225  case kR2S:

10803  case kExprTableGet: {
10804  bool is_table64 = module_->tables[instr.optional.index].is_table64();
10805  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_TableGet, s2s_Table64Get, is_table64,
10806  instr.pc);
10807  EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index);
10808  is_table64 ? I64Pop() : I32Pop();

10810  break;
10811  }

10813  case kExprTableSet: {
10814  bool is_table64 = module_->tables[instr.optional.index].is_table64();
10815  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_TableSet, s2s_Table64Set, is_table64,
10816  instr.pc);
10817  EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index);
10818  RefPop();
10819  is_table64 ? I64Pop() : I32Pop();
10820  break;

10823 #define LOAD_CASE(name, ctype, mtype, rep, type) \
10824  case kExpr##name: { \
10825  switch (mode) { \
10826  case kR2R: \
10827  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(r2r_##name, r2r_##name##_Idx64, \
10828  is_memory64_, instr.pc); \
10829  EmitMemoryOffset(instr.optional.offset); \
10830  return RegMode::k##type##Reg; \
10831  case kR2S: \
10832  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(r2s_##name, r2s_##name##_Idx64, \
10833  is_memory64_, instr.pc); \
10834  EmitMemoryOffset(instr.optional.offset); \
10835  type##Push(); \
10836  return RegMode::kNoReg; \
10837  case kS2R: \
10838  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2r_##name, s2r_##name##_Idx64, \
10839  is_memory64_, instr.pc); \
10840  EmitMemoryOffset(instr.optional.offset); \
10841  MemIndexPop(); \
10842  return RegMode::k##type##Reg; \
10843  case kS2S: \
10844  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_##name, s2s_##name##_Idx64, \
10845  is_memory64_, instr.pc); \
10846  EmitMemoryOffset(instr.optional.offset); \
10847  MemIndexPop(); \
10848  type##Push(); \
10849  return RegMode::kNoReg; \
10850  } \
10851  break; \
10852  }
10853  LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem8S, int32_t, int8_t, kWord8, I32);
10854  LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem8U, int32_t, uint8_t, kWord8, I32);
10855  LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem16S, int32_t, int16_t, kWord16, I32);
10856  LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem16U, int32_t, uint16_t, kWord16, I32);
10857  LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem8S, int64_t, int8_t, kWord8, I64);
10858  LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem8U, int64_t, uint8_t, kWord16, I64);
10859  LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem16S, int64_t, int16_t, kWord16, I64);
10860  LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem16U, int64_t, uint16_t, kWord16, I64);
10861  LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem32S, int64_t, int32_t, kWord32, I64);
10862  LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem32U, int64_t, uint32_t, kWord32, I64);
10863  LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem, int32_t, int32_t, kWord32, I32);
10864  LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem, int64_t, int64_t, kWord64, I64);
10865  LOAD_CASE(F32LoadMem, Float32, uint32_t, kFloat32, F32);

10869 #define STORE_CASE(name, ctype, mtype, rep, type) \

11246  case kExprStructGet:
11247  case kExprStructGetS:
11248  case kExprStructGetU: {
11249  bool is_signed = (instr.opcode == wasm::kExprStructGetS);
11250  const StructType* struct_type = module_->struct_type(
11251  ModuleTypeIndex({instr.optional.gc_field_immediate.struct_index}));
11252  uint32_t field_index = instr.optional.gc_field_immediate.field_index;
11253  ValueType value_type = struct_type->field(field_index);
11254  ValueKind kind = value_type.kind();
11255  int offset = StructFieldOffset(struct_type, field_index);
11256  switch (kind) {
11257  case kI8:
11258  if (is_signed) {
11259  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I8SStructGet, instr.pc);
11260  } else {
11261  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I8UStructGet, instr.pc);
11262  }
11263  RefPop();
11264  EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11265  I32Push();
11266  break;
11267  case kI16:
11268  if (is_signed) {
11269  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I16SStructGet, instr.pc);
11270  } else {
11271  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I16UStructGet, instr.pc);
11272  }
11273  RefPop();
11274  EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11275  I32Push();
11276  break;
11277  case kI32:
11278  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I32StructGet, instr.pc);
11279  RefPop();
11280  EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11281  I32Push();
11282  break;
11283  case kI64:
11284  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I64StructGet, instr.pc);
11285  RefPop();
11286  EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11287  I64Push();
11288  break;
11289  case kF32:
11290  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_F32StructGet, instr.pc);
11291  RefPop();
11292  EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11293  F32Push();
11294  break;
11295  case kF64:
11296  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_F64StructGet, instr.pc);
11297  RefPop();
11298  EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11299  F64Push();
11300  break;
11301  case kS128:
11302  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_S128StructGet, instr.pc);
11303  RefPop();
11304  EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11305  S128Push();
11306  break;
11307  case kRef:
11308  case kRefNull:
11309  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_RefStructGet, instr.pc);
11310  RefPop();
11311  EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11312  RefPush(value_type);
11313  break;
11314  default:
11315  UNREACHABLE();
11316  }
11317  break;
11318  }
11319 
11320  case kExprStructSet: {
11321  const StructType* struct_type = module_->struct_type(
11322  ModuleTypeIndex({instr.optional.gc_field_immediate.struct_index}));
11323  uint32_t field_index = instr.optional.gc_field_immediate.field_index;
11324  int offset = StructFieldOffset(struct_type, field_index);
11325  ValueKind kind = struct_type->field(field_index).kind();
11326  switch (kind) {
11327  case kI8:
11328  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I8StructSet, instr.pc);
11329  EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11330  I32Pop();
11331  break;
11332  case kI16:
11333  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I16StructSet, instr.pc);
11334  EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11335  I32Pop();
11336  break;
11337  case kI32:
11338  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I32StructSet, instr.pc);
11339  EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11340  I32Pop();
11341  break;
11342  case kI64:
11343  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I64StructSet, instr.pc);
11344  EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11345  I64Pop();
11346  break;
11347  case kF32:
11348  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_F32StructSet, instr.pc);
11349  EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11350  F32Pop();
11351  break;
11352  case kF64:
11353  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_F64StructSet, instr.pc);
11354  EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11355  F64Pop();
11356  break;
11357  case kS128:
11358  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_S128StructSet, instr.pc);
11359  EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11360  S128Pop();
11361  break;
11362  case kRef:
11363  case kRefNull:
11364  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_RefStructSet, instr.pc);
11365  EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11366  RefPop();
11367  break;
11368  default:
11369  UNREACHABLE();
11370  }
11371  RefPop(); // The object to set the field to.
11372  break;
11373  }
11374 
11375  case kExprArrayNew: {
11376  uint32_t array_index = instr.optional.gc_array_new_fixed.array_index;
11377  const ArrayType* array_type =
11378  module_->array_type(ModuleTypeIndex({array_index}));
11379  ValueType element_type = array_type->element_type();
11380  ValueKind kind = element_type.kind();
11381 
11382  // Pop a single value to be used to initialize the array.
11383  switch (kind) {
11384  case kI8:
11385  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I8ArrayNew, instr.pc);
11386  EmitI32Const(array_index);
11387  I32Pop(); // Array length.
11388  I32Pop(); // Initialization value.
11389  break;
11390  case kI16:
11391  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I16ArrayNew, instr.pc);
11392  EmitI32Const(array_index);
11393  I32Pop();
11394  I32Pop();
11395  break;
11396  case kI32:
11397  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I32ArrayNew, instr.pc);
11398  EmitI32Const(array_index);
11399  I32Pop();
11400  I32Pop();
11401  break;
11402  case kI64:
11403  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I64ArrayNew, instr.pc);
11404  EmitI32Const(array_index);
11405  I32Pop();
11406  I64Pop();
11407  break;
11408  case kF32:
11409  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_F32ArrayNew, instr.pc);
11410  EmitI32Const(array_index);
11411  I32Pop();
11412  F32Pop();
11413  break;
11414  case kF64:
11415  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_F64ArrayNew, instr.pc);
11416  EmitI32Const(array_index);
11417  I32Pop();
11418  F64Pop();
11419  break;
11420  case kS128:
11421  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_S128ArrayNew, instr.pc);
11422  EmitI32Const(array_index);
11423  I32Pop();
11424  S128Pop();
11425  break;
11426  case kRef:
11427  case kRefNull:
11428  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_RefArrayNew, instr.pc);
11429  EmitI32Const(array_index);
11430  I32Pop();
11431  RefPop();
11432  break;
11433  default:
11434  UNREACHABLE();
11435  }
11436  // Push the new array.
11437  RefPush(
11438  ValueType::Ref(module_->heap_type(ModuleTypeIndex({array_index}))));
11439  break;
11440  }
11441 
11442  case kExprArrayNewFixed: {
11443  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_ArrayNewFixed, instr.pc);
11444  uint32_t length = instr.optional.gc_array_new_fixed.length;
11445  uint32_t array_index = instr.optional.gc_array_new_fixed.array_index;

11449  module_->array_type(ModuleTypeIndex({array_index}));

11456  case kI16:
11457  case kI32:

11459  break;

11464  F32Pop();

11466  case kF64:
11467  F64Pop();
11468  break;
11469  case kS128:
11470  S128Pop();
11471  break;
11472  case kRef:
11473  case kRefNull:
11474  RefPop();
11475  break;
11476  default:
11477  UNREACHABLE();
11478  }
11479  }
11480  // Push the new array.
11481  RefPush(
11482  ValueType::Ref(module_->heap_type(ModuleTypeIndex({array_index}))));
11483  break;
11484  }

11491  ModuleTypeIndex array_index{instr.optional.index};

11493  ValueType::Ref(module_->heap_type(ModuleTypeIndex({array_index}))));
11494  break;

11795  case kExprRefCast:
11796  case kExprRefCastNull: {
11797  bool null_succeeds = (instr.opcode == kExprRefCastNull);
11798  HeapType target_type = HeapType::FromBits(
11799  instr.optional.gc_heap_type_immediate.heap_type_bit_field);
11800  ValueType resulting_value_type = ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
11801  target_type, null_succeeds ? kNullable : kNonNullable);
11802 
11803  ValueType obj_type = slots_[stack_.back()].value_type;
11804  DCHECK(obj_type.is_object_reference());
11805 
11806  // This logic ensures that code generation can assume that functions
11807  // can only be cast to function types, and data objects to data types.
11808  if (V8_UNLIKELY(TypeCheckAlwaysSucceeds(obj_type, target_type))) {
11809  if (obj_type.is_nullable() && !null_succeeds) {
11810  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_AssertNotNullTypecheck, instr.pc);
11811  ValueType value_type = RefPop();
11812  EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
11813  RefPush(resulting_value_type);
11814  } else {
11815  // Just forward the ref object.
11816  }
11817  } else if (V8_UNLIKELY(TypeCheckAlwaysFails(obj_type, target_type,
11818  null_succeeds))) {
11819  // Unrelated types. The only way this will not trap is if the object
11820  // is null.
11821  if (obj_type.is_nullable() && null_succeeds) {
11822  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_AssertNullTypecheck, instr.pc);
11823  ValueType value_type = RefPop();
11824  EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
11825  RefPush(resulting_value_type);
11826  } else {
11827  // In this case we just trap.
11828  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_TrapIllegalCast, instr.pc);
11829  }
11830  } else {
11831  if (instr.opcode == kExprRefCast) {
11832  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_RefCast, instr.pc);
11833  } else {
11834  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_RefCastNull, instr.pc);
11835  }
11836  EmitI32Const(instr.optional.gc_heap_type_immediate.heap_type_bit_field);
11837  ValueType value_type = RefPop();
11838  EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
11839  RefPush(resulting_value_type);
11840  }
11841  break;
11842  }
11843 
11844  case kExprRefTest:
11845  case kExprRefTestNull: {
11846  bool null_succeeds = (instr.opcode == kExprRefTestNull);
11847  HeapType target_type = HeapType::FromBits(
11848  instr.optional.gc_heap_type_immediate.heap_type_bit_field);
11849 
11850  ValueType obj_type = slots_[stack_.back()].value_type;
11851  DCHECK(obj_type.is_object_reference());
11852 
11853  // This logic ensures that code generation can assume that functions
11854  // can only be cast to function types, and data objects to data types.
11855  if (V8_UNLIKELY(TypeCheckAlwaysSucceeds(obj_type, target_type))) {
11856  // Type checking can still fail for null.
11857  if (obj_type.is_nullable() && !null_succeeds) {
11858  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_RefIsNonNull);
11859  RefPop();
11860  I32Push(); // bool
11861  } else {
11862  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_RefTestSucceeds);
11863  RefPop();
11864  I32Push(); // bool=true
11865  }
11866  } else if (V8_UNLIKELY(TypeCheckAlwaysFails(obj_type, target_type,
11867  null_succeeds))) {
11868  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_RefTestFails);
11869  RefPop();
11870  I32Push(); // bool=false
11871  } else {
11872  if (instr.opcode == kExprRefTest) {
11873  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_RefTest);
11874  } else {
11875  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_RefTestNull);
11876  }
11877  EmitI32Const(instr.optional.gc_heap_type_immediate.heap_type_bit_field);
11878  ValueType value_type = RefPop();
11879  EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
11880  I32Push(); // bool
11881  }
11882  break;
11883  }

12045  EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(
12046  s2s_I64AtomicWait, s2s_I64AtomicWait_Idx64, is_memory64_, instr.pc);
12047  I64Pop(); // timeout
12048  I64Pop(); // val
12049  EmitMemoryOffset(instr.optional.offset);
12050  MemIndexPop(); // memory index
12051  I32Push();
12052  break;
12053 
12054  case kExprAtomicFence:
12055  EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_AtomicFence);
12056  break;
